# Layout System — Car & Driver Marketplace

## Container

The global `.container` class is defined in `src/index.css`:
- `max-width: var(--max-width-container)` (1280px)
- `margin: 0 auto`
- `padding: 0 var(--spacing-4)` (16px sides)
- At 768px+: `padding: 0 var(--spacing-6)` (24px sides)

Always wrap page content in `.container`. Never set max-width manually.

## Page Structure

```
<div className="page-name">          {/* Full-width wrapper */}
  <section className="page-name__hero">
    <div className="container">       {/* Centered content */}
      ...
    </div>
  </section>
  <section className="page-name__content">
    <div className="container">
      ...
    </div>
  </section>
</div>
```

- Full-width backgrounds go on the section
- Content constraint goes on `.container` inside the section
- Page-level padding: `var(--spacing-8)` (32px) top/bottom on sections

## Grid Patterns

### Card grids (deals, vehicles, rankings)
```css
.page__grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  gap: var(--spacing-4);
}

@media (max-width: 900px) {
  .page__grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
}

@media (max-width: 600px) {
  .page__grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
}
```

### Two-column layout (detail pages)
```css
.page__layout {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 360px;
  gap: var(--spacing-6);
}

@media (max-width: 1024px) {
  .page__layout { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
}
```

## Breakpoints

No CSS variables for breakpoints. Use these consistent values:

| Name | Value | Usage |
|------|-------|-------|
| Mobile small | max-width: 480px | Single column, compact spacing |
| Mobile | max-width: 600px | Single column grids |
| Tablet | max-width: 768px | 2-column grids, reduced padding |
| Tablet landscape | max-width: 900px | Card grid 3→2 columns |
| Desktop small | max-width: 1024px | Sidebar collapse |
| Desktop | max-width: 1200px | Full layout |
| Wide | min-width: 1401px | Extra spacing |

## Sticky Elements

- **Header**: `position: sticky; top: 0; z-index: 1000`
- **Toolbar/filters**: `position: sticky; top: 0; z-index: 50` (below header)
- **Sidebar**: `position: sticky; top: calc(var(--header-height) + var(--spacing-4))`

## Z-Index Layers (informal scale — no tokens)

| Range | Usage |
|-------|-------|
| 1–10 | Local stacking within components |
| 20–50 | Overlapping elements, sticky toolbars |
| 100 | Tooltips, popovers |
| 200 | Dropdowns |
| 1000 | Header |
| 1001–1002 | Modals, overlays |
| 1100 | Toast notifications |
| 10000 | Skip link |

## Spacing Patterns

- **Section padding**: `var(--spacing-8)` (32px) top/bottom
- **Card padding**: `var(--spacing-4)` (16px)
- **Card gap**: `var(--spacing-4)` (16px) in grids
- **Content gap**: `var(--spacing-6)` (24px) between major sections
- **Inline spacing**: `var(--spacing-2)` (8px) between inline elements
- **Tight spacing**: `var(--spacing-1)` (4px) for tight groups

## Responsive Rules

1. Mobile-first: base styles are mobile, add complexity with min-width
2. Card grids: 1 column → 2 columns (768px) → 3 columns (900px+)
3. Sidebars: collapse below 1024px
4. Font sizes: scale down headings on mobile (e.g., 4xl → 3xl)
5. Spacing: reduce section padding on mobile (`--spacing-6` instead of `--spacing-8`)
6. Images: always `width: 100%; height: auto` or use `aspect-ratio`
7. Touch targets: minimum 44px height for interactive elements on mobile
